<item>
            <title>[CXF-5305] STSClient does not send Renewing element in renewal RequestSecurityToken message</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5305</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;STSClient does not add a Renewing element to the RequestSecurityToken message when performing a renew, regardless of the value of sendRenewing (or allowRenewing or allowRenewingAfterExpiry).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This does not prevent prevent a renewal from being renewed because that is allowed by default, but it does prevent a renewal from being renewed after expiry (OK=true attribute) when that option is enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The client is also unable to prevent a renewal from being renewable (using the Allow=false attribute) however I&apos;m not sure the client would ever attempt that anyway since the same restriction would be on the originally issued token so you would never get that far.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See AbstractSTSClient#renew(SecurityToken) line 955 which I believe needs code similar to AbstractSTSClient#issue(String,String,String,String) lines 745-755.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
